# My status

Three modes:
- **list** (default) — show the user's open prod tasks. Read-only.
- **send** (`send` argument, or user asks to post the status) — take all open
  tasks ordered by **sequence**, estimate them, propose which close **today**
  (each with estimate + link); show that plan **plus the remaining backlog** so
  the user can confirm/swap; re-estimate any swap; then post **only today's
  planned tasks — no backlog** to the team chat **after an explicit go**.
  Read-only against Odoo (writes only to Teams).
- **rebalance** (`rebalance` argument, or invoked by the pipeline when a new
  task enters scope) — re-estimate the user's open assigned tasks and **shift
  their `date_deadline`** so the schedule absorbs the newly-added work, then
  write the new deadlines/estimates back. The **only** mode that writes to
  Odoo, and only `date_deadline` + estimate fields on the **user's own** open
  assigned tasks (scope guard below).

## Identity — read first

Read memory node `nodes/user_identity.md` (memory dir → see MEMORY.md): full
name, Odoo login, default project id, "Current ticket" stage, Teams status
chatId, required Teams auth. **Never hardcode a person** — the skill must work
for any teammate with their own identity node. An explicit login argument
overrides the node (list mode only).

